commit.message:
AlexaServer: End the session after a command

This affects all requests except for the help intent.

Keep session open for the help intent

This is according to https://developer.amazon.com/docs/custom-skills/voice-interface-and-user-experience-testing-for-a-custom-skill.html#cert-providing-help
pom.xml: Fix Alexa Skills Kit dependency

pom.xml: Exclude spring-boot-starter-logging

Running the application from IntelliJ IDEA was giving this error:
LoggerFactory is not a Logback LoggerContext but Logback is on the classpath.
Either remove Logback or the competing implementation (class
org.slf4j.impl.SimpleLoggerFactory) Object of class
[org.slf4j.impl.SimpleLoggerFactory] must be an instance of class
ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext

Solution taken from:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23984009/disable-logback-in-springboot

Also see:
https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current-SNAPSHOT/reference/htmlsingle/#howto-configure-log4j-for-logging

Maybe Alexa Skills Kit introduced slf4j and that resulted in the error?

pom.xml: Add Alexa Skills Kit dependency

This will be used for request validation. See:
https://developer.amazon.com/docs/custom-skills/host-a-custom-skill-as-a-web-service.html#verifying-that-the-request-was-sent-by-alexa

WebSocket server: generate connection ID

Also, start the websocket server from the Application class that starts the web
server instead of having a separate application for it.
Add request model and parser class
